// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception
//
// T033 — R1 alt/any case-arrow alignment per formatting-rules.contract.md §1.
//
// Frozen invariant: in an `alt` block with N cases, the `:`
// separators all align to the column ONE SPACE past the longest
// condition's last char. With three cases of varying width:
//
//     alt {
//         phase == IDLE    : reg := 0;
//         phase == RUNNING : reg := 1;
//         phase == DONE    : reg := 2;
//     }
//
// T052 (R1) made this GREEN: `lib/Fmt/LayoutPlanner.cpp` adds
// `formatNode(AltBlock)` / `formatNode(AnyBlock)` (delegating to
// the shared `formatCondCaseBlock` helper) plus four
// recursion-only overrides — `FuncDefn`, `SeqBlock`,
// `ParallelBlock` (the parser models a brace-enclosed `func`
// body as a `ParallelBlock`, NOT a `SeqBlock`), and the existing
// `ModuleBlock` — so the rule actually fires on a nested
// `module > func > { alt { ... } }` shape.
//
// **Identifier-name workaround.** The canonical example in
// `formatting-rules.contract.md` §1 uses `state` for the
// case-machine variable and `reg` for the assignment target —
// BOTH of which are reserved keywords in NSL (lang.ebnf §15).
// The lexer produces `tk_state` / `tk_reg`, not `tk_identifier`,
// when it sees the barewords; putting either in expression /
// transfer-LHS position triggers a separate, pre-existing parser
// bug that locks the parser in a recovery loop (the formatter
// then OOM-kills under any reasonable memory budget). This
// fixture works around the bug by substituting `phase` (for
// `state`) and `q` (for `reg`); both are plain identifiers. The
// R1 rule itself is unchanged — alignment math is
// identifier-agnostic. Restoring the canonical spellings here
// will be safe once the keyword-as-identifier parser bug is
// fixed.

// RUN: echo 'module m { func f { alt { phase == IDLE : q := 0; phase == RUNNING : q := 1; phase == DONE : q := 2; } } }' | nsl-fmt --stdin | FileCheck %s
// CHECK: phase == IDLE    :
// CHECK: phase == RUNNING :
// CHECK: phase == DONE    :
